result.execSummary:
The defendant ASHLI C SACKETTE was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: -Consecutive to any other sentence. No credit.

superMiscConds.notes: -Court orders the fine and costs in this file shall be paid from all funds received into the defendant's prison accounts in accordance with prison policy. If any fines and/or costs remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.  If probation/supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.  You may be randomly tested for compliance. 
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample. 

NOT A CONDITION OF PROBATION BUT NEEDS TO BE COMPLETED WHEN ON EXTENDED SUPERVISION: Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department. Defendant to contact the Green Lake County Jail 920-294-4059 Ext #6.

of Initial Appearance, Plea & Sentencing hearing held on May 3, 2022, before Hon Mark T. Slate - Circuit Court Judge, by Karen Blair - Court Reporter
Letter to the defendant dated 05/06/2022 with court forms to be filled out and one copy returned.

8:54 AM Defendant ASHLI C SACKETTE appeared by video, (video not working) in custody.  Attorney Matthew Steven McElroy in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant can hear the Court but is not able to see the Court and requests to proceed without video. Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading. Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count and as repeater. Court instructs defendant of his/her right to an attorney. Defendant requests to proceed without counsel. Court instructs defendant of his/her right to counsel. Defendant waives right to counsel. Court accepts waiver. DA recites agreement - upon a plea to count 1, will dismiss the repeater with bifurcated prison sentence and the balance of the counts will be dismissed and read-in. Defendant concurs, will plead NO CONTEST. ADA states the information will be filed. Court makes statement to the defendant re: information, will be emailed down but will not have it for today's hearing. Court goes over right to appear in person. 

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights. Court goes over the elements of each offense. Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty. Court instructs defendant regarding deportation. (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions. 

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST. Court finds the plea is made knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently. Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea. Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1, striking the repeater and orders counts 2,3 & 4 be dismissed and read-in. Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today. Sentencing statement by ADA. Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

-2 years WSP, with 1 year of Initial Confinement and 1 year of Extended Supervision, consecutive to any other sentence.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:

-Court costs.
-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.  You may be randomly tested for compliance. 
-AODA and any follow-up.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample. 

Court finds the defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
No sentence credit.

+Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.
